Marvell (c) Linux User-Space SDK
---------------------------------------------------

musdk is a light-weight user I/O driver for Marvell Packet Processor.
The purpose of this driver library is to create a wrapper for the
native implementation of Open Data Plane for Armada 8K Packet Processor.

Coding style:
Linux Kernel Coding Style
https://www.kernel.org/doc/Documentation/CodingStyle

checkpatch.pl that can be used to test for
adhering to the coding style rule.

i.e.
./checkpatch.pl -f --no-tree ../../libs/musdk/apps/pp_app.c

Steps to build and run the MUSDK library:

0. Build Linux:

a. Make sure the Linux is build with the following configuration flags:
	CONFIG_MVPP2X=m
	CONFIG_UIO=y
b. Apply all patches found <musdk-src-dir>/patches/linux

1. Built the PP2-tmp kernel module and install it

> cd <musdk-src-dir>/modules/pp2_tmp
> export LDFLAGS=""
> make -C $KDIR M=$PWD
> make DESTDIR=~/target/sdk install

1. Built the UIO kernel module and install it

> cd <musdk-src-dir>/modules/uio
> make
> make DESTDIR=~/target/sdk install

2. Build the MUSDK and install it
> cd <musdk-src-dir>
> ./autogen.sh
> ./configure --host=aarch64-linux-gnu
> make -j8
> make DESTDIR=~/target/sdk install

3. Running MUSDK apps:

insert <mv_pp_uio.ko> in a running kernel and run the application

